row.entry:
This is one of a package of 5 integrated Directives. The Universal Service Directive provides for:
A process for reviewing the scope of universal service obligations;
Specific users and consumers rights where necessary;
The continuation of existing measures to ensure the availability of leased lines in the EU until competition in these services develops;
National Regulator Authorities (NRAs) to take measures on behalf of users and consumers; and
Interoperability of consumer digital television equipment.
